    "b) Functionality of HFMs still seems monotonous and it is challenging to meet some complex clinical demands.",
    "For example, chronic disease management will involve information from multiple departments and various modalities [410], and require the implementation of multiple clinical procedures such as diagnosis, intervention, prognosis, etc.",
    "Although some generalist HFMs have shown promise in various clinical settings [10], [31], they are powerless to meet such complex multi-modal, multi-task requirements.",
    "4) Adaptability:The adaptability of foundational models determines their ability to adapt to downstream scenarios, which remains a significant challenge in HFM.",
    "a) One aspect is the transferring ability for downstream tasks."
